ExecutorInvalidOperationLength(uint256,u.details: Mismatch between the parameters length for an operation call.

FailedInnerCall().details: A call to an address target failed. The target may have reverted.

CallExecuted(bytes32,uint256,address,uin.details: Emitted when a call is performed as part of operation `id`.

execute(address,uint256,bytes,bytes32).details: Execute an (ready) operation containing a single transaction. Emits a {CallExecuted} event. Only owner can execute, usually Governor Contract.

executeBatch(address[],uint256[],bytes[].details: Execute an (ready) operation containing a batch of transactions. Emits one {CallExecuted} event per transaction in the batch. Only owner can execute, usually Governor Contract.

hashOperation(address,uint256,bytes,byte.details: Returns the identifier of an operation containing a single transaction.

hashOperationBatch(address[],uint256[],b.details: Returns the identifier of an operation containing a batch of transactions.

init(address).details: For use after cloning a contract, where initial memory is 0
